{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501391","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501391"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:29:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:29:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1757"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1757"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.37,0.14,0.39,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1757"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84788"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1757"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1757"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69084"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"174"},{"type":"tags","id":"1074"},{"type":"tags","id":"1150"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3343"},{"type":"tags","id":"3870"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2218"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2434"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6269"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10890"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42390"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43099"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84788","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/84788"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 66-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-month history of hand tremor that is present at rest but improves with movement. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHis wife, who accompanies him, reports that he has been seeing children playing in their house when there are none present. She is particularly concerned about his increasing confusion in the evenings and disturbed sleep pattern. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is asymmetric rigidity in his upper limbs, more pronounced on the left side.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate medication for managing cognitive impairment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Haloperidol","Levodopa","Quetiapine","Donepezil","Selegiline"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features consistent with Dementia with Lewy bodies (DLB), including parkinsonism (resting tremor, asymmetric rigidity), visual hallucinations, and fluctuating cognition with evening confusion (\u0027sundowning\u0027). The presence of sleep disturbance suggests possible REM sleep behaviour disorder, another characteristic feature.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDonepezil\u003C/strong\u003E, an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor, is the most appropriate choice for managing cognitive symptoms in DLB. These medications can improve cognition and reduce hallucinations, making them first-line treatment for cognitive symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHaloperidol\u003C/strong\u003E is absolutely contraindicated in DLB. Up to 50% of DLB patients are severely sensitive to antipsychotics, particularly first-generation agents, which can cause severe extrapyramidal side effects and neuroleptic malignant syndrome, even at low doses.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EQuetiapine\u003C/strong\u003E, while sometimes used at low doses for severe behavioural symptoms in DLB when other options have failed, should not be first-line therapy due to antipsychotic sensitivity. Acetylcholinesterase inhibitors should be tried first.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELevodopa\u003C/strong\u003E may help manage parkinsonian motor symptoms in DLB but does not address the cognitive impairment. Lower doses are typically needed compared to Parkinson\u0027s disease, and response is often less robust.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelegiline\u003C/strong\u003E, a monoamine oxidase B inhibitor, is used in Parkinson\u0027s disease but has no role in managing the cognitive symptoms of DLB.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Dementia with Lewy bodies requires at least two of: visual hallucinations, parkinsonism, REM sleep behaviour disorder, and fluctuating cognition.","Acetylcholinesterase inhibitors are first-line treatment for cognitive symptoms in Lewy body dementia.","Antipsychotics, especially first-generation agents, should be avoided due to severe sensitivity reactions in Lewy body dementia."],"references":["Dementia. In: eTG complete [online]. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. 2021 Mar. Available at: https://www.tg.org.au","Taylor JP, McKeith IG, Burn DJ, Boeve BF, Weintraub D, Bamford C, Allan LM, Thomas AJ, O\u0027Brien JT. New evidence on the management of Lewy body dementia. Lancet Neurol. 2020 Feb;19(2):157-169. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7017451/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69084"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1757"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69084","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/69084"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-11T11:01:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-11T11:01:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id"